The 28-day mortality of the ALI patients was 27.7%. The 28-day mortality was significantly different among the three ACE genotypes (17.4%, 26.8%, and 64.3% for II, ID, and DD, respectively; p = 0.013). Patients with the DD genotype had a lower possibility of survival for 28 days as compared with other groups (Fig. 1
). Table 4
showed the results of survival analysis and demonstrated that DD genotype (Odd ratio, 8.80; 95% confidence interval, 1.75–44.06; p = 0.008) was the significant independent prognostic factors for the 28-day outcome.
